07 Aug 2019 20:08






This doesn't fully follows up on the implications it raises in how the SCP manifests/demanifests and the logs were gratuitous. If there was a rhyme or reason as to what they were trying to achieve, even if it was a failed attempt at medical treatment, I didn't get it. There's more story to be mined in giving it an orange/grey interpretation of what counts as a medical emergency. You could also maybe throw in some classist elements in terms of whether or not people can afford ambulances having anything to do with how these entities manifest. But it's just straightforward and violent and there doesn't seem to be any reason for it. The body modifications are creative but they're not enough to make me enjoy this.








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






